Dataset Information

This project uses surveillance video datasets for anomaly detection.

Primary Dataset Used:
CUHK Avenue Dataset

Dataset Source:
https://www.cse.cuhk.edu.hk/leojia/projects/detectabnormal/dataset.html

Dataset Description:
The Avenue dataset contains surveillance videos recorded in an outdoor campus environment. 
It includes normal pedestrian movements used to train the anomaly detection model.

Dataset Preparation:
1. Training videos are converted into frames using the video_to_frames.py script.
2. Frames are stored inside dataset/train.
3. The autoencoder model is trained only on normal frames.
4. During real-time detection, abnormal frames produce higher reconstruction error.

Note:
Due to GitHub file size limitations, only a small sample dataset is included in this repository.
